      "writtenOn": "2019-04-25T19:47:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I guess technically by the contract it doesn\u0027t really matter what Skia returns here. If we return no it just means the client still owns the non-existent semaphores and if we return yes then skia owns the non existent semaphores. Either way the caller doesn\u0027t have anything to do.\n\nSaying that, it looks like internally we may be a little inconsistent on what we return if no semaphores are provided. I could go back in and add logic to make it consistent one way or the other, but it really shouldn\u0027t change much on the client side. I really want to keep this return value only having real meaning if semaphores were passed in. I can at least make the comments here more descriptive to say if no semaphores are passed in the return value should be ignored.",
      "parentUuid": "1f981d08_99a1754a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 277,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 277,
        "endChar": 54
      },
